---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AI-Fit-Scan Dataset" description="Analysis of 161 fitness apps — 61 with AI claims">
  <div class="container-content py-16">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <span class="section-label mb-4">Dataset</span>
      <h1 class="mb-2">AI-Fit-Scan Dataset</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)] mb-6">A systematic analysis of AI claims in fitness applications.</p>

      <!-- Overview stats -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="card-static text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-ink)]">161</div>
          <div class="text-[0.55rem] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase">Apps Analyzed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-static text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-ink)]">61</div>
          <div class="text-[0.55rem] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase">With AI Claims</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-static text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-ink)]">3</div>
          <div class="text-[0.55rem] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase">Label Categories</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-static text-center">
          <div class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-ink)]">T/F/Q</div>
          <div class="text-[0.55rem] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase">AI Label Types</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- About the dataset -->
      <div class="card-static mb-6">
        <h2 class="font-sans text-[0.7rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">About</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
          The AI-Fit-Scan dataset catalogs 161 fitness and health applications available on iOS and Android app stores, documenting their use of artificial intelligence features. Each app was reviewed for AI-related claims and categorized by functionality.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)] leading-relaxed">
          Of the 161 apps analyzed, <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">61 (37.9%)</strong> made explicit AI claims. These claims were classified into three label types: <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">True (T)</strong>, <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">False (F)</strong>, and <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Questionable (Q)</strong>, based on whether the claimed AI functionality was actually implemented.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Key findings -->
      <div class="card-static mb-6">
        <h2 class="font-sans text-[0.7rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Key Findings</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)]">
          <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">37.9%</strong> of fitness apps make AI claims — suggesting widespread adoption of AI marketing in the fitness domain.</li>
          <li>Claims fall into <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">three categories</strong>: actual AI implementation (T), overstated claims (F), and ambiguous/misleading descriptions (Q).</li>
          <li>This dataset informed the motivation for FitCalib-Bench: if apps claim AI but don't deliver, how reliable is the AI advice they provide?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Download -->
      <div class="card-static mb-6 bg-[var(--color-page-warm)]">
        <h2 class="font-sans text-[0.7rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-muted)] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Download</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)] mb-3">The full dataset is available for research use.</p>
        <span class="btn btn-sm opacity-60 cursor-default">CSV download — coming soon</span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
